Flutter has some official third party plugins. But if you want to use those then you should check the availability of those plugin.
I am sharing my approach on how I have approached this.

1. You can add package in pubspec.yaml file.
   flutter:
    sdk: flutter

   and then run below command.
     dart pub get --verbose

   it will check and install package that you have asked for.

2. If you want to use google login, follow below links
 https://pub.dev/packages/google_sign_in
 https://pub.dev/packages/google_mobile_app_auth

3. If you are interested in firebase integration then follow below links
https://pub.dev/packages/firebase_core
https://firebase.flutter.dev/docs/installation/android#add-firebase-as-a-dependency

4.  Firebase has many feature. For example, It have a messaging services also and it support email and password for authentication.
    To integrate it follow below links.
     https://firebase.google.com/docs/auth/flutter
     https://pub.dev/packages/cloud_firestore
     
     To add cloud firestore follow below link.
     https://firebase.google.com/docs/database/android/start#set-up

5. If you want to add 3rd party plugins then follow below link
   https://github.com/fluttercommunity/plus_plugins

Hope it will help you. Thankyou!